    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-05T09:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-05T09:54:00-05:00" n="869"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d869">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.51/5–545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-05T18:00:00+03:06"
                            >May 5, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>193. ReDepts No. 130, May 3, 6 p.m. While 2 months ago King Abdul Aziz would have
                    been quite receptive to proposals confined to subject of my approaching visit I
                    expect him to demand information on matters of greater urgency to him now (<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>) subsidy program for 1945 (Department’s No. 125, April
                    7 [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>], 6 p.m.) and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                    expectations of long range financial aid (Department’s No. 283, December 24, 2
                        p.m.<note n="95" xml:id="d869fn95">
                        <ref target="frus1944v05#pg_759">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1944, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 759</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>If possible can Department authorize me to make any statement on either subject
                    during this visit? Locust plague, non-delivery of cereals and spare parts, lack
                    of any indication whether his budget will be balanced disturb him profoundly
                    Minister of Finance<note n="96" xml:id="d869fn96">Abdullah Suleiman.</note>
                    informs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
